description: Five people convicted over the journalist's murder have been given 20-year prison terms instead.
title: Jamal Khashoggi murder: Saudi court commutes death sentences
title_page: Jamal Khashoggi murder: Saudi court commutes death sentences - BBC News
maintext: The journalist was forcibly restrained after a struggle and injected with a large amount of a drug, resulting in an overdose that led to his death, according to the prosecution. His body was then dismembered and handed over to a local "collaborator" outside the consulate. The remains were never found.
